              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment was carried out at the",
                "ISAC2 facility at TRIUMF"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Target consisted of set of four 208Pb foils, backed by",
                "Al foils. Stacked target thicknesses were 0.585, 0.856,",
                "1.215 and 0.721mg/cm2.",
                "The Al foil thicknesses were 5.033 and 0.98mg/cm2."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "82-PB-208",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.99
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "82-PB-207",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.007
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "82-PB-206",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.003
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Each Pb target-degrader assembly was at the",
                "center of a cubical vacuum chamber, where four",
                "300-mm2 Canberra PIPS silicon detectors viewed the",
                "target-degrader assembly."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "KINDT"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Proton beams with energy of 500 MeV and",
                "intensity of approx. 70 mu-A struck Ta metal",
                "production targets. Beams of radioactive 11Li were",
                "extracted with energies up to 18.4 keV,",
                "mass-separated by passage through two dipole magnets,",
                "and accelerated to their final energy by",
                "radio-frequency quadrupole and drift tube linear",
                "accelerators. The \"center-of-target\" 11Li beam energies",
                "were 26.1, 27.4, 28.5 and 32.7MeV in the four cubes"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The 11Li beam was pulsed on for less than 5",
                "ns and shut off for 172 ns, during which time the",
                "alpha decay of any stopped evaporation residue was",
                "measured. Product nuclei were identified by alpha",
                "particle energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
